<HEADLINE>
COWBOYS OWNER POSITIVE ABOUT QUENTIN CORYATT'S RETURN
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By Ray Buck and Clarence E. Hill Jr. 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Linebacker Quentin Coryatt's chronic Achilles' tendinitis is not
being viewed as a lingering preseason negative around Valley Ranch,
but rather ``a bonus'' for the Cowboys whenever Coryatt gets
healthy, defensive coordinator Dave Campo said yesterday.
</P>
<P>
   The Cowboys never thought Coryatt was retiring.
</P>
<P>
   Owner Jerry Jones didn't have to talk the 29-year-old Coryatt
out of retirement during their one-hour meeting on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   ``He was just worried about what his teammates might be thinking
of him and his situation,'' Jones said. ``He's the type of player
who worries that he might be letting somebody down. People who have
high expectations often are harsh on themselves.''
</P>
<P>
   Darren Hambrick, who has impressed coach Chan Gailey and the
Cowboys coaching staff all summer with his change in attitude and
his improved work ethic, has become the starter at strongside
linebacker. Hambrick, a 1998 fifth-round pick, has had eight
tackles in four games this preseason.
</P>
<P>
   Campo said, ``I'm comfortable with the guys we got. I told our
players to just think of \RCoryatt's injury absence\S as a bonus
when we get him, not a negative.''
</P>
<P>
   Gailey remembers Coryatt reeking havoc against Pittsburgh when
Gailey was a coach with the Steelers and Coryatt played for the
Indianapolis Colts.
</P>
<P>
   ``If we have a chance of getting a healthy Quentin Coryatt at
some point, we'll take that,'' Gailey said. ``I'm not worried. I
understand Quentin's situation. I feel for him.''
</P>
<P>
   Coryatt signed a one-year contract with a two-year option with
the Cowboys in April after being released by the Colts and spending
all last season out of football because of reconstructive shoulder
surgery.
</P>
<P>
   His frustration is compounded by his not having played since
1997. His last full season was '95.
</P>
<P>
   The former Texas A&AMP;M star has a $400,000 base salary. He was
given a $1-million signing bonus, but Jones isn't worried about the
investment.
</P>
<P>
   ``We're going to be patient and conservative,'' Jones said.
\Nsubheds:No interest in Jones
</P>
<P>
   Owner Jerry Jones said the Cowboys have made no contact with the
Tampa Bay Buccaneers regarding defensive tackle Marvin Jones.
</P>
<P>
   According to a source, the Cowboys were one of three teams to
express interest in acquiring the former North Carolina star.
</P>
<P>
   But Jerry Jones said the Cowboys are happy with the defensive
linemen on the roster and have not talked to Tampa Bay about
shoring up the position. \Nsubheds:Briefly Cowboys coach Chan
Gailey said he will wait until game time before deciding whether
receiver Ernie Mills (hamstring) and linebacker Randall Godfrey
(ankle) will play against the Jaguars.
</P>
<P>
   Running back Chris Warren, who is still hampered by a sore groin
and suffered a neck strain last Sunday against the Denver Broncos,
is expected to play against the Jaguars.
</P>
<P>
   The Cowboys signed rookie free-agent cornerback Marvin Love, who
was released by the St. Louis Rams, and waived cornerback
LaDouphyous McCalla.
</P>
<P>
   Tight end Hayward Clay had successful surgery yesterday to
repair a torn anterior cruciate ligament in his left knee.
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
