   TEN-USOPEN (New York) _ Goran Ivanisevic was one of several
relieved winners on a relatively drama-free afternoon where
56th-ranked Tara Snyder's 7-5, 6-3 upset of the 43d-ranked Mirjana
Lucic, 17, the Wimbledon semifinalist, was the main surprise and
17th-seeded Felix Mantilla was the only deposed seed. The Spaniard
fell to Magnus Norman, 1-6, 6-1, 6-2, 6-4. By Robin Finn. With
photos.
