<SLUG> BC-OSTLER-COLUMN-SFCHRON </SLUG>
  
 3 CANDIDATES IN SEARCH OF A CLUE  &HT;     By SCOTT OSTLER 
 &HT;     c.1999 San Francisco Chronicle  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Only in San Francisco: a political debate with a mosh pit.
</P>
<P>
   Other random notes from Da Big Mayoral Debate:
</P>
<P>
   If we have to have an audience, somebody should tell the folks
that there's a very fine line between enthusiastic spectators and
sheeplike political suck-ups acting as a human laugh track.
</P>
<P>
   The only way any of the three candidates will advance from this
debate to the actual election will be through social promotion.
</P>
<P>
   It figures that Mayor Brown, who enjoys music, would show up
with his own private sound system, complete with stereo speakers
Woofer Jordan and Tweeter Reilly. At this rate, Brown is going to
lock up the sympathy vote.
</P>
<P>
   Next time, to even the battle, Brown should bring along his tiny
clone, Mini Mayor.
</P>
<P>
   The debate committee made mistakes, of course. Somebody forgot
to bring the foam bats for Reilly and Jordan to use on the mayor.
</P>
<P>
   Credit goes to Willie's mustache, making a plucky comeback from
a brutal shaving. Advice to Brown on 'stash: Don't leave home
without it.
</P>
<P>
   At one point Brown was interrupted by a heckler, and it turned
out to be Reilly.
</P>
<P>
   Did I go out for popcorn and miss the parts where Jordan and
Reilly attacked one another?
</P>
<P>
   Seriously, it was a lively debate, with some real issues raised
and discussed, some real emotion shown. Of course, in political
debate, the evaluation bar is set lower than the bar at a cockroach
limbo contest.
</P>
<P>
   Wake me when they get to the talent competition: Jordan dancing
the shower scene from ``Flashdance,'' Reilly speed-writing a
48-page book on how he'll fix the Giants' bullpen, &LR;  and Willie
tap-dancing.
</P>
<P>
   The Brown-Jordan-Reilly debate winner: You mean after all that
babbling, posturing, pontificating and cliche-spouting, someone
actually wins?
</P>
<P>
   WHAT PART of mandatory summer school does the Oakland Board of
Education not understand?
</P>
<P>
   And what do they now tell the 7,000 kids who went to summer
school after being told they had to attend in order to be promoted?
Can these gullible children get a refund on their summer?
</P>
<P>
   Referring to Oakland, state schools Superintendent Delaine
Eastin said, ``That is a district in deep, deep yogurt.''
</P>
<P>
   I hadn't heard that expression, but assume it's worse than being
in deep clover but better than being in deep doo-doo.
</P>
<P>
   THE GOOD fathers at St. Boniface in the Tenderloin blessed the
taxis Wednesday, and I hope the program proves successful and is
expanded to Muni Metro, which might require a full-scale exorcism.
</P>
<P>
   And what about a blessing of the taxi passengers, where each cab
will stop at the curb in front of St. Boniface and the padre will
place a Dramamine tablet on the tongue of each rider?
</P>
<P>
   A San Francisco cab trip is the Bay Area's most gut-wrenching
thrill ride.
</P>
<P>
   ``Why do 2 of every 3 cabbies here drive like they're trying to
make you sick?'' wonders visitor James Smith.
</P>
<P>
   It's a San Francisco tradition, James. To pass taxi driver
training school here, you have to place a Caesar salad in the back
seat of your cab and toss it without touching it.
</P>
<P>
   SAY IT AIN'T SO: Beanie Babies will be retired at the end of
this year, the company just informed consumers, whose panic is
expected to plunge the world into massive economic (and spiritual)
depression.
</P>
<P>
   My financial advisor  &LR; adviser tells me that the Beanie Baby news
could open the door for a gigantic pet rock revival.
</P>
<P>
   REDNECKS ain't what they used to be. Nichole Bradshaw was
driving down 101 Wednesday and saw a pickup truck with a gun rack
in the rear window. And in the gun rack? Rolled-up blueprints.
</P>
<P>
   A CRUISE SHIP and a tanker collided recently, and Walt
Sledzieski is amazed that this kind of accident doesn't happen
regularly, especially right here in the bay. Walt notes a recent
Chronicle ``Ship Traffic'' report that listed one ship's port of
origin as ``unknown'' and three other ships' destinations as
``unknown.''
</P>
<P>
   If these guys don't know where they're coming from or where
they're going, little wonder there are collisions.
</P>
<P>
   Even worse, most of the captains are men, which means they won't
stop to ask directions.
</P>
<P>
   IT TURNS OUT that the scientists who claimed they cloned Dolly
the sheep were pulling the wool over our eyes. We fell for it, and
don't we feel sheepish.
</P>
<P>
   A DNA analysis proved that Dolly isn't a true clone, but what is
known as a chimera. Kind of a c &LR; Clone- &LR;  l &LR; Lite.
</P>
<P>
   Isn't it crazy? DNA testing nails Dolly, while O.J. walks the
streets a free man.
</P>
<P>
   Dolly and her chimera, in homage to fraudulent duos everywhere,
will henceforth be known as Wooli Vanooli.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
