<SLUG> BC-FBC-OKLAHOMA-CAPSULE-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
WITH OKLAHOMA PREVIEW
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By MIKE JONES 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   OKLAHOMA Coach: Bob Stoops (first season).
</P>
<P>
   1998: 5-6 (3-5, T-4 in South Division.
</P>
<P>
   Returning starters: 5 on offense, 5 on defense (different
systems).
</P>
<P>
   What has to go right: Stoops and his staff have to get the most
out of the talent at hand, which is better than some in the Big 12
but not on a par with the best teams.
</P>
<P>
   What can't go wrong: Like most thin teams, injuries could prove
costly. Though this staff plans to play a lot of players on both
sides of the ball, it looks like Josh Heupel is the only
quarterback with a proper grasp of coordinator Mike Leach's
multiple, pass-oriented offense.
</P>
<P>
   Update: Heupel completed 17 of 29 passes for 222 yards and two
touchdowns in Saturday's major scrimmage in Tulsa. The scrimmage
before a crowd of 10,000-plus enabled OU to write a $38,000 check
to the American Red Cross for continued relief for the state's
tornado victims. ... OU had previously drawn 27,000 for a scrimmage
in Norman. ... The offensive line remains a big concern. Returning
starting guard Jason Bronson had to give up football because of
recurring concussions. Guard Ryan Allen missed all of last week
with a strained calf. And tackle Scott Kempenich is still having
problems with the foot in which he suffered a stress fracture last
spring, though Stoops hopes he'll be available for the Sept. 11
opener against Indiana State. Safety Ontei Jones, who tied for the
team lead last season with 100 tackles, likewise has not worked
much in August because he reinjured an ankle that kept him out of
spring drills.
\Nsubheds:1999 SCHEDULE Sept. 11 Indiana St. 6:30 p.m. Sept. 18
Baylor 11:30 a.m. Sept. 25 at Louisville 6 p.m. Oct. 2 at Notre
Dame 12:30 p.m. Oct. 9 vs. Texas TBD Oct. 23 Texas A&AMP;M 2 p.m. Oct.
30 at Colorado TBD Nov. 6 Missouri 2 p.m. Nov. 13 at Iowa St. 1
p.m. Nov. 20 at Texas Tech 1 p.m. Nov. 27 Oklahoma St. 2 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   _At Dallas
\Nsubheds:WHERE THEY'RE RANKED ``The Sporting News'' 67 ``Sports
Illustrated'' 55 ``Star-Telegram'' 58
</P>
</TEXT>
