   ``I think we've got a good nucleus of players we should be able
to win with. The thing we've got to do is get the most out of the
talent we have. If we do that and we have a few guys who
overachieve, we've got enough to win.''
</P>
<P>
   Stoops' straightforward approach early won over a team
desperately searching for leadership.
</P>
<P>
   ``Coach Stoops is a great guy,'' senior safety Rodney Rideau
said. ``He preaches discipline, getting the job done and he
preaches excellence. That's what we want to hear, what it takes to
win. There's no doubt he's brought structure and organization back
to the team. He sets goals and encourages us to set goals _ and to
live by them.
</P>
<P>
   ``He came from a winning tradition. And hopefully, he'll bring
it back to us.''
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
