<P>
   MEANS-COLUMN (Washington) _ John F. Kennedy Jr. has been dead
for a month and half, and his face still adorns slick magazine and
book covers. But already reality is intruding on the nostalgia. His
sister is trying to save his failing magazine, his mother-in-law is
positioning herself for a possible wrongful death suit and
criticism mounts that his own bad judgment was at fault in the
crash. By MARIANNE MEANS.
