   NYSE-IPO (New York) _ New York Stock Exchange board meets on
proposal to take exchange public. By Richard A. Oppel Jr.
</P>
<P>
   BUDWEISER-RECALL (Madrid) _ Anheuser-Busch recalls all bottled
Budweiser beer from 12 European countries, saying there was a
chance slivers of glass could break off from the rim of the bottle.
</P>
<P>
   MARKET (New York) _ At 1:55 p.m., stocks were lower. The Dow
Jones industrial average was down 200 points, the S&AMP;P 500 down 20
points and the Nasdaq composite down 25 points. The 30-year bond
was now yielding 6.14 percent. In Europe, markets were also lower
with London down 1.20 percent and Frankfurt down 2.39 percent. The
Nikkei closed down 0.96 percent, while the Hang Seng index ended
down 1.30 percent. By Robert D. Hershey Jr.
</P>
<P>
   CREDIT (New York) _ Credit market developments. By Robert
Hurtado.
