<TEXT>
<P>
   Weekend Section stories from The New York Times News Service for
Friday, Sept. 3.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FEATURES &LR;
</P>
<P>
   HOLYWOOD-EDGE (Undated) _ When Albert Brooks, playing a
successful middle-aged screenwriter in ``The Muse,'' is bluntly
informed by a baby-faced executive reptile at Paramount Pictures
that his writing has lost its ``edge,'' it is the career equivalent
of a death sentence. Only magic of a particularly glitzy and silly
Hollywood sort can help him regain it. Edge. Oh to have it! To be
on the cutting edge, to be, as they say, edgy! If you're pitching a
movie or a television show to a Hollywood baby mogul nowadays, it
had better have edge, or you're history, kiddo. But what is that
exactly? After running neck and neck with the sweet old-fogyish
``hip'' to evoke what's progressive, contemporary and (excuse the
cliche) ahead of the curve, edge seems to have pulled ahead. It
has, as they say, the edge. By Stephen Holden.
</P>
<P>
   JAR-THEATER-REVIEW (New York) _ ``Jar the Floor.'' Reviewed by
Jesse McKinley.
</P>
<P>
   MET-CHINESE-EXHIBIT (New York) _ ``The Artist as Collector:
Masterpieces From the C.C. Wang Family Collection,'' an exhibition
of nearly 100 paintings, many of exceptional beauty, at the
Metropolitan Museum of Art. By Holland Cotter.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; MOVIES &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ANIMALS-FILM-REVIEW (Undated) _ ``All The Little Animals'':
Jeremy Thomas, direcrtor; with Christian Bale and John Hurt.
Reviewed by Stephen Holden.
</P>
<P>
   BEDROOMS-FILM-REVIEW (Undated) _ ``Bedrooms and Hallways'': Rose
Troche, director; with Kevin McKidd, Simon Callow, Hugo Weaving,
Jennifer Ehle and Christopher Fulford. Reviewed by Stephen Holden.
</P>
<P>
   BEIRUT-FILM-REVIEW (Undated) _ ``West Beirut'': Ziad Doueriri,
director; war brews in 1975 Lebanon. Reviewed by Janet Maslin.
</P>
<P>
   FILMS4KIDS (Undated) _ Assessing the current cinema for children
of different ages.
</P>
<P>
   AT-THE-MOVIES (Hollywood) _ News of the silver screen. By
Bernard Weinraub.
</P>
<P>
   MOVIES-IN-BRIEF (Undated) _ Capsule reviews by New York Times
critics.
</P>
<P>
   HOMEVIDEO (Undated) _ Short items on what's news in home video
and short reviews of what's new in home video. By Peter M. Nichols.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; OTHER ENTERTAINMENT &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   YES-BOOK-REVIEW (Undated) _ ``Yes We Have No,'' by Nick Cohn
(Knopf). Reviewed by Michiko Kakutani.
</P>
<P>
   TV-WEEKEND (Undated) _ Ron Wertheimer spotlights the weekend's
television fare: Sunday on Showtime, ``Happy Face Murders.''
</P>
<P>
   ANTIQUES-COLUMN (New York) _ The Antiques Column. By Wendy
Moonan.
</P>
<P>
   ALBUM-OF-THE-WEEK (Undated) _ Spotlighting a new album.
</P>
