   BBO-UMPIRES (Philadelphia) _ Latest news developments concerning
the 22 umpires who now find themselves out of a job. Story will
attempt to get Commissioner Bud Selig to speak about baseball's
position in this unusual labor confrontation. By Murray Chass.
</P>
<P>
   BBO-UMPIRES-LASTGAME (Undated) _ There were some poignant scenes
on Wednesday night as the careers of some veteran major league
umpires came to a close, at least for now. In Houston, the Mets'
Orel Hershiser ran over to home-plate umpire Bob Davidson and
patted him on the back. In St. Louis, Mark McGwire handed Frank
Pulli the game ball. By Jack Curry.
</P>
