SAN FRANCISCO _  RIBS  _ Ribs are a passion. Everyone has a
favorite marinade or barbecue sauce recipe for making them, and
many argue about where to buy the best take-out. They've also been
showing up in Bay Area restaurants in several forms _ and they're
being served way beyond the usual American red sauce barbecue
variety. &HT;    Main story is followed by rib basics sidebar, three perfect
barbecue sauces and recipes. 
 By Robin Davis  
 c. 1999 The San Francisco Chronicle  
<TEXT>
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
SAN FRANCISCO _  &UR; SECRETS-Ribs &LR;  _ With ingredients such as
chocolate, orange and sherry you might think that Heidi Krahling,
chef/owner of Insalata's, was making a dessert rather than a main
course. But when the meaty short ribs come out of the oven after
three hours they're rich, juicy and absolutely delicious.
<P>
   This is the latest installment of the regular column describing
what makes a Bay Area restaurant's dish a success, we'll tell how
to make it.
</P>
<P>
   With recipe, chef's secrets for success.
</P>
