   BUSH-EDUC (Los Angeles) _ George W. Bush outlined his education
plans Thursday. He would apply strict standards to public schools
receiving federal aid for poor children and penalize those not
making progress by converting their aid into, in effect, vouchers
that pupils could take to private schools. By James Sterngold.
(Summary from wires)
