that awaits the 80,000 fans, players, coaches and referees as they
spend about 4 hours in direct sun. How hot will it be? Why play
during the day so early in the year when the tradition used to be
early season night games. (TV is the answer.) And what should
people do to cope? We find out what people can bring in the gate,
such as bottled water, to fortify themselves against sunstroke.
(Jayson, Austin American-Statesman)
