entrepreneuer who drops out of big business to pursue an arcane
labor of love is a familiar type in the West, but in Russia, Pyotr
Suspitsyn is as rare as his books. Stepping out of this age of
greed, Suspitsyn, 35, is working to revive a tradition of making
books so exquisite that each is a work of art. By Neela Banerjee.
