<P>
   CHINESE-IMMIGRANTS (VICTORIA, B.C.) _ They spent $38,000 each
for the privilege of spending 60 days at sea in a rickety ship,
being fed a bowl of rice and two glasses of water a day, heading
for what they were told was a Land of Gold in Canada where they
could easily earn enough to repay their cost of passage. Instead,
some 450 Chinese nationals aboard three ships seized in the past
month off British Columbia are pondering their fate in a Canadian
Armed Forces holding facilitiy near Victoria.
