<P>
   (NYT1) NEW YORK -- Sept. 2, 1999 -- NY-POLICE-BUSCH, 09-01 --
Netanya Ullman, Gidone Busch's fiancee, at a gathering of Orthodox
Jews in Brooklyn's Borough Park neighborhood on Tuesday. The police
officers who shot and killed Busch in Brooklyn on Monday evening
said Busch attacked them with a hammer outside his tiny basement
apartment. On that hammer, Busch, 31, a devoutly religious man who
prayed so loudly the neighbors complained, had carved the four
Hebrew letters signifying the name of God. (Edward Keating/New York
Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   The New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
