 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-ISRAEL-GERMANY-CONCERT-NYT (moved on Monday, Aug. 30)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Because of an
editing error, an article on Tuesday about a joint concert
performance by German and Israeli musicians at Buchenwald on Sunday
misattributed a 19th-century Romantic tradition exploited by the
Nazis. The passage in question should have read: ``This humanism
and enlightenment of Goethe gave way during the 19th century to
expressions of Romantic cultural nationalism that the Nazis would
later seize on and distort.'' Goethe was not among the Romantic
nationalist writers invoked by the Nazis.
</P>
</TEXT>
